## Test Anti-Pattern Audit: `ProductCatalogTests.cs`

This is a textbook **coverage-touching** test suite. Every production method is invoked (achieving ~95% line coverage), but almost no behavior is actually verified. These tests would still pass if the production code returned garbage, deleted everything, or silently corrupted data.

---

### 🔴 CRITICAL — Assertion-Free Tests (Coverage Touching)

| # | Test Method | Problem |
|---|-------------|---------|
| 1 | `AddProduct_Works` (L17-21) | **Zero assertions.** Calls `AddProduct` and declares victory. A no-op implementation would pass. |
| 2 | `UpdatePrice_Works` (L33-35) | **Zero assertions.** Never checks the price actually changed. Production could save the *old* price and this test passes. |
| 3 | `RemoveProduct_Works` (L38-42) | **Zero assertions.** Never verifies the product is actually gone after removal. |
| 4 | `GetProductCount_Works` (L63-66) | **Zero assertions.** Doesn't even check the count value. Could return -1. |
| 5 | `ApplyBulkDiscount_Works` (L68-74) | **Zero assertions.** The most complex logic in the class (price arithmetic) is completely unverified. A discount of 200% or 0% would pass. |
| 6 | `ImportFromCsv_Works` (L83-88) | **Zero assertions.** Never verifies any product was actually created from the CSV. |

**Fix pattern:**
```csharp
// Before (coverage-touching)
[TestMethod]
public void UpdatePrice_Works()
{
    _catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m));
    _catalog.UpdatePrice("SKU-001", 14.99m);
}

// After (actually verifies behavior)
[TestMethod]
public void UpdatePrice_ChangesStoredPrice()
{
    _catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m));
    _catalog.UpdatePrice("SKU-001", 14.99m);
    var updated = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
    Assert.AreEqual(14.99m, updated!.Price);
}
```

---

### 🟠 HIGH — Shallow/Trivial Assertions (`Assert.IsNotNull` only)

| # | Test Method | Problem |
|---|-------------|---------|
| 7 | `GetProduct_Works` (L23-29) | Only checks `IsNotNull`. Never verifies the *correct* product was returned — wrong SKU, wrong name, wrong price would all pass. |
| 8 | `SearchProducts_Works` (L45-52) | Only checks `IsNotNull` on the list. Empty list passes. List with wrong products passes. Filtering logic is unverified. |
| 9 | `GetAllProducts_Works` (L55-60) | Only checks `IsNotNull`. Doesn't verify the count or contents. |
| 10 | `ExportToCsv_Works` (L76-82) | Only checks `IsNotNull`. An empty string or malformed CSV passes. |

**Fix pattern:**
```csharp
// Before (trivial assertion)
[TestMethod]
